		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>Louise Erdich, Han Kang, David Streitfeld, and more: 20 new books out today!</h1>
			</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/juliahass/"  title="Julia Hass">Julia Hass</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">March 24, 2026</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p>Officially: it is spring. Does that mean we can finally put our winter coats and scarves away? Time will tell. Until then, until we know for sure the snow has gone for good, let&#8217;s just count our blessings and look towards the bounty of books coming out today. Louise Erdich delivers a new collection of stories that has had prepubs raving, Han Kang&#8217;s speeches have been collected in Hogarth&#8217;s <em>Light and Thread</em>, and a definitive biography of Larry McMurtry all grace our shelves today. Dive into the rest of the list below, and happy reading!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="268026" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=268026" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss.jpg" data-orig-size="350,529" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="python&amp;#8217;s kiss" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-268026" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss-198x300.jpg" alt="python's kiss" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/pythons-kiss.jpg 350w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Louise Erdich, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780063375000" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Python&#8217;s Kiss</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Harper)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A staggering sense of empathy infuses the stories. With its range of voices and styles, this puts Erdrich’s powers on full display.”<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264488" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/han-kang-tr-maya-west-e-yaewon-and-paige-aniyah-morris-light-and-thread/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread.jpg" data-orig-size="1105,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Han Kang, tr. Maya West, e. yaewon and Paige Aniyah Morris, Light and Thread" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-221x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-754x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264488" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-221x300.jpg" alt="Han Kang, tr. Maya West, e. yaewon and Paige Aniyah Morris, Light and Thread" width="221" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-221x300.jpg 221w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-754x1024.jpg 754w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-768x1043.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-44x60.jpg 44w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread-37x50.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Han-Kang-tr.-Maya-West-e.-yaewon-and-Paige-Aniyah-Morris-Light-and-Thread.jpg 1105w" sizes="(max-width: 221px) 100vw, 221px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Han Kang, trans. by Maya West, e. yaewon and Paige Aniyah Morris, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798217155033" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Light and Thread</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Hogarth)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;From Nobel Prize winner Han Kang comes her first work of nonfiction published in English—a singular collection of writings including her inspiring Nobel Lecture.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>From the publisher</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264487" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/david-streitfeld-western-star/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="David Streitfeld, Western Star" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264487" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-199x300.jpg" alt="David Streitfeld, Western Star" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Streitfeld-Western-Star.jpg 993w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>David Streitfeld, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780063234888" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Western Star: The Life and Legends of Larry McMurtry</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Mariner)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Bring[s] us as close as we are ever likely to get to a man whose range and depth of achievement has few parallels in American letters.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Benjamin Moser</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="268061" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/louise-erdich-han-kang-david-streitfeld-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/attachment/9798217086481/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481.jpeg" data-orig-size="298,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Beheading Game, Rebecca Lehmann" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-268061" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481-199x300.jpeg" alt="The Beheading Game, Rebecca Lehmann" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/9798217086481.jpeg 298w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rebecca Lehmann, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798217086481" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Beheading Game</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Crown)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Magic, romance, revenge, and an utterly irresistible heroine—this book is an instant classic.”<br />
<em>–</em>Lev Grossman</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="268062" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/louise-erdich-han-kang-david-streitfeld-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/howflowersmadeourworld/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld.jpg" data-orig-size="795,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="David George Haskell, How Flowers Made Our World:" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-268062" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/howflowersmadeourworld.jpg 795w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>David George Haskell, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593834961" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>How Flowers Made Our World: The Story of Nature&#8217;s Revolutionaries</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Viking)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Through deep research and lyrical prose, Haskell triumphantly recasts the role of flowers as foundational to humanity.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264496" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/jake-skeets-horses/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses.jpg" data-orig-size="986,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Jake Skeets, Horses" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-673x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264496" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-197x300.jpg" alt="Jake Skeets, Horses" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-673x1024.jpg 673w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-768x1168.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jake-Skeets-Horses.jpg 986w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Jake Skeets, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781639551521" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Horses: Poems</em></a></strong><br />
